name: Chicken Sausage Rolls Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat fan forced oven to 200Â°C and line trays with baking paper
Combine mince, cheeses, carrot, zucchini, egg, corn and mixed herbs and mix together well

Cut pastry sheets in half and brush long edges of pastry with whisked egg. Spoon portion of mince mix into middle of pastry sheet and roll pastry over the top to fully cover it. Pressing edges together firmly. Optional: You then cut each 'roll' in half.
Brush the tops of the sausage rolls with more of the whisked egg and place on the baking trays.
Bake in oven for 25-30 mins until pastry is golden
